snippet.title: Lost City Day 1 Release!! 2004 Runescape
snippet.description:
Experience authentic old-school gameplay with perilous adventures and epic Nostalgia to a more simpler time. 
👉You Can Play 2004Scape Here 👉https://2004scape.org/
Check out other 04 content here! https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ehdLWZvJqpE&list=PLFIB0MVZ-tJtD7a3eB8Mn3BCDLHe0deSh&index=11

👉This is an emulation of RuneScape as it was in 2004.
It exists for the sake of nostalgia and preservation of the game's history.
this is a non-profit no-donation open-source hobby project.

👉It is not representative of today's RuneScape and does not involve any of their live services. You cannot play Old School RuneScape here or buy RuneScape gold! This is a fan-made project and is not affiliated with Jagex Ltd. The assets within belong wholly to Jagex. The website content and assets were obtained via archive.org snapshots from May/June 2004. The client and its assets were obtained from old computer backups. The server uses no official code and was written in NodeJS/JavaScript, based on observations and historical archives.

👉https://2004scape.org/
👉https://discord.gg/Jwn566ZVpu
👉https://lostcity.rs/

This is a recorded video of Lost City's (a RuneScape emulation and preservation project) 2004scape. Authenticity driven server, with probably the most accurate engine ever created, based on the 225 client-build revision dated May 18, 2004. The content code is heavily researched down to the finest of detail; tens of thousands of videos, images, fansites, and archives used as sources. If you want to check out the project yourself: https://2004scape.org/

This channel is designed to archive the oldest RuneScape footage posted online.
👉Play Runescape now, a free to play (F2P) online MMORPG: https://www.runescape.com

👉Play Oldschool Runescape now, a free to play (F2P) online MMORPG:
http://oldschool.runescape.com/

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Ds8qtrBQb-g&list=PL6YrD0Gvbmk7vquLaZPT2oUW8uO_Prvxz
